    Introduction

    Welcome to the Inkredo API! You must be a premium customer to use the api

    Authentication

    Inkredo uses API keys to allow access to the API. You can register a new Inkerdo API key at our main webapp. After completing the KYC process and subscribing to our services, you can go to the settings page and obtain the keys from the api section

    Inkredo expects the API key to be included in all API requests to the server in a header that looks like the following:

    access-id: your_access_id

    access-key: your_access_key

    You must replace your_access_id and your_access_key with your personal access-key and access-id.

    Bank statement analysis

    Create borrower

    curl --request POST \
  --url <URL>/api/v2/dashboard/create_borrower/ \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --header 'access-id: your_access_id' \
  --header 'access-key: your_access_key' \
  --data '{"name":"Ram GANDHI"}'

    The above command returns JSON structured like this:

    {
    "success": true,
    "message": "Borrower created successfully",
    "borrowerId": "5bb36bc3e38eb85f7207461d"
}

    This endpoint creates a new borrower. You need to save this borrowerId for later use.

    HTTP Request

    POST <URL>/api/v2/dashboard/create_borrower

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type application/json
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Body

    Parameter Required Description
    name true Name of the borrower

    Supported banks

    curl --request GET \
  --url <URL>/api/v2/parser/supported_banks \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --header 'access-id: your_access_id' \
  --header 'access-key: your_access_key'

    The above command returns JSON structured like this:

    {
    "banks": [
        {
            "code": "HDFC",
            "displayName": "HDFC Bank",
            "support": {
                "csv": true,
                "excel": true,
                "pdf": true
            }
        },
        {
            "code": "ICICI",
            "displayName": "ICICI Bank",
            "support": {
                "csv": false,
                "excel": false,
                "pdf": true
            }
        },
    ]
}

    This endpoint retrieves a list of all banks with information on the file type currently supported.

    HTTP Request

    GET <URL>/api/v2/parser/supported_banks

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type application/json
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    This endpoint parsers and analysis a bank statement.

    Users should switch to a newer version v2!

    HTTP Request

    POST <URL>/api/v1/parser/

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type multipart/form-data
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Body

    Parameter Required Description
    bank true bank code obtained from supported banks api above
    statement true bank statement file to be analysed
    borrowerId true id of the borrower created earlier
    pdfPassword false password of the pdf

    Parser v2

    The above command returns JSON structured like this:

    This endpoint parsers and analysis a bank statement.

    v2 supports parsing of statements that have multiple accounts in them. The response of v1 is wrapped in a account number key in v2.

    HTTP Request

    POST <URL>/api/v2/parser/

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type multipart/form-data
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Body

    Parameter Required Description
    bank true bank code obtained from supported banks api above
    statement true bank statement file to be analysed
    borrowerId true id of the borrower created earlier
    pdfPassword false password of the pdf

    Reanalyse bank statement

    POST <URL>/api/v2/parser/reanalyse/

    Body

    {"borrowerId":"5bb20ba98b583b0b9cf1e13b"}

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type application/json
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Response

    same as the parser api

    Generate excel report link

    curl -X POST \
  <URL>/api/v2/parser/excel/ \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'access-id: your_access_id' \
  -H 'access-key: your_access_key' \
  -d '{
    "borrowerId":"5c6a5cbe8e4b510b60e7633a"
}'

    The above command returns JSON structured like this:

    {
    "success": true,
    "message": "Download link generated successfully",
    "downloadLink": "https://inkredo-reports.amazonaws.com/reprot.xlsx"
}

    This endpoint provides a link to download the report in excel format. To download the excel file, you can visit the link returned in downloadLink of the response body.

    HTTP Request

    POST <URL>/api/v2/parser/excel

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type application/json
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Body

    Parameter Required Description
    borrowerId true borrower ID
    The downloadLink will expire after 10 minutes

    Extract PII

    curl -X POST \
  <URL>/api/v2/extract_pii/ \
  -H 'Content-Type: multipart/form-data' \
  -H 'access-id: your_access_id' \
  -H 'access-key: your_access_key' \
  -F 'pdf=@/path/to/file.pdf'

    The above command returns JSON structured like this:

    {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
        "account_number": "111111111111111111",
        "ifsc": "IFSC0123456",
        "metadata": {
            "author": "Virender",
            "creation_date": "25 Nov 2016 16:25:54 +0530",
            "creator": "Adobe Acrobat 11.0.10",
            "modification_date": "25 Nov 2016 16:31:37 +0530",
            "producer": "GPL Ghostscript 9.06"
        },
        "name": "Mohammad Lee",
        "pan": "ABCD1234F",
        "statement_period": {
            "from": "01/04/2018",
            "to": "30/04/2018"
        }
    }
}

    This endpoint is for extracting PII from a bank statement. PII includes information like client's account number, IFSC, etc.

    HTTP Request

    POST <URL>/api/v2/extract_pii

    Headers

    Name Value
    Content-Type multipart/form-data
    access-id your_access_id
    access-key your_access_key

    Body

    Parameter Required Description
    pdf true PDF file object

    Errors

    The Inkredo API uses the following error codes:

    Error Code Meaning
    400 Bad Request -- Your request is invalid.
    404 Not Found -- The specified api/page could not be found.
    500 Internal Server Error -- We had a problem with our server. Try again later.
    500 Internal Server Error -- We had a problem with our server. Try again later.
    503 Service Unavailable -- We're temporarily offline for maintenance. Please try again later.
